The paper discusses the issue of algorithmic bias in biometric systems, which is a topic that falls under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper specifically focuses on the bias in face recognition algorithms, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely category, followed by cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.HC.
